            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Just for reference:\n\n> The id-match loop is O(N) over targets keys, called per-message. For typical configs (< 10 entries) it's negligible. If users ever build very large mapping tables, the linear scan + per-key regex could become noticeable.\n",
            "commit_id": "e645947c4fa6f207f36c8be4e7faff274b462d8c",
            "created_at": "2026-05-12T15:17:24Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -392,23 +399,32 @@ local in_pager = false -- Whether the pager is or will be the current window.\n ---@param id integer|string\n ---@param trigger string\n function M.msg_show(kind, content, replace_last, _, append, id, trigger)\n+  -- Match configured target mappings as Lua pattern to ID:\n+  local k, v, id_target = next(type(id) == 'string' and ui.cfg.msg.targets or {})\n+  while k and not id_target do\n+    id_target = id:match(k) and v\n+    k, v = next(ui.cfg.msg.targets, k)\n+  end",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39734#discussion_r3227616383",
